Renowned South African author and activist Achmat Dangor has died aged 71. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Renowned South African author and activist Achmat Dangor has died aged 71. The former CEO of Nelson Mandela Foundation is also ANC Deputy Secretary-General, Jessie Duarte's brother The ANC has sent its heartfelt condolences to the Dangor family.
